            <div type="commentary">
                <p><!--commented out pending revision-->
                    <!--63.5 cm x 16 cm. Honorific erected by the artists (technitai) of Aphrodite Hilara, granting proxenia to a Roman benefactor (euergetos), Ateilios Sarranos Sopater (Atilius Sarranus Sopater). Note that one of the two eponymous priests of the decree is calls Gaios Arrios, son of Aulos (probably). As manganaro notes, this decree and the other publ'd by himself and Gentili with v. similar context, show the penetration of Roman elements, or at least those with c'ship, and the infl. of Roman elites with greek articstic associations, which in turn are flourishing in this period.--></p>
            </div>
